cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual data and proposes a method to improve the performance of human interaction prediction using spatial and temporal features.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) networks to capture the structural feature and introduces a new ranking score fusion method to combine the models.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with predicting human interactions, which is a task that can be useful in human-robot interaction and other AI applications.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper mentions human-robot interaction as one of the applications of human interaction prediction.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with video data and proposes a method to improve the performance of human interaction prediction.
